            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the<strong> crispy cumin beef</strong> to a plate and set aside</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p><p>Return the pan (and any oil left from the mince) to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained black beans</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant – these are your <strong>smoky beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1255.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1255.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
